\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.4}{\ignorespaces Overview of the glucose system in the RCC model. The continuous glucose field $C(\mathbf  {x}, t)$ is maintained through a cycle of: (1) glucose injection from blood vessels, (2) 3D diffusion via Fick's Law, (3) natural decay, (4) consumption by tumor and immune cells, and (5) gradient computation for chemotaxis. Feedback loops modulate cell growth and activity based on local glucose availability.}}{46}{figure.caption.17}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:glucose_system}{{4.4}{46}{Overview of the glucose system in the RCC model. The continuous glucose field $C(\mathbf {x}, t)$ is maintained through a cycle of: (1) glucose injection from blood vessels, (2) 3D diffusion via Fick's Law, (3) natural decay, (4) consumption by tumor and immune cells, and (5) gradient computation for chemotaxis. Feedback loops modulate cell growth and activity based on local glucose availability}{figure.caption.17}{}}
