\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10.5}{\ignorespaces Box plot distributions of final tumor cell counts across all treatment scenarios (n=20 per group). The bimodal distributions reflect the stochastic nature of tumor-immune dynamics, where early random events determine whether tumors are eliminated or escape immune control. Note the dramatic variance within groups and the shift toward lower tumor burdens with effective treatments.}}{123}{figure.caption.54}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:empirical-tumor-boxplot}{{10.5}{123}{Box plot distributions of final tumor cell counts across all treatment scenarios (n=20 per group). The bimodal distributions reflect the stochastic nature of tumor-immune dynamics, where early random events determine whether tumors are eliminated or escape immune control. Note the dramatic variance within groups and the shift toward lower tumor burdens with effective treatments}{figure.caption.54}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10.6}{\ignorespaces Survival rates across all treatment scenarios stratified by biological sex. Female patients demonstrate consistently higher survival rates across most treatment conditions, with the ICI+TKI combination achieving the highest survival rate (65\%) observed in the study. The data reveal complex sex-treatment interactions that would be missed by single-seed analysis.}}{124}{figure.caption.55}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:empirical-survival-rate}{{10.6}{124}{Survival rates across all treatment scenarios stratified by biological sex. Female patients demonstrate consistently higher survival rates across most treatment conditions, with the ICI+TKI combination achieving the highest survival rate (65\%) observed in the study. The data reveal complex sex-treatment interactions that would be missed by single-seed analysis}{figure.caption.55}{}}
